design at high level JIRA application


Designing a high-level JIRA-like application involves defining the core modules, their responsibilities, and how they interact. Hereâ€™s a high-level system design overview covering architecture, modules, components, database schema (briefly), scalability, and extensibility.

ğŸ¯ Goals
A JIRA-like application should support:

Project and issue tracking

Custom workflows

Role-based access control

Dashboards and reports

Notifications and integrations

Scalable multi-tenant architecture

